FBIS3-49677 "dreeu009_y_94008" FBIS-EEU-94-009 Document Type:Daily Report 13 Jan 1994 YUGOSLAVIA Vojvodina Fuel Shortage Threatens Spring Sowing LD1301103294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in Serbo-Croatian 0553 GMT 13 Jan 94 LD1301103294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service Language: Serbo-Croatian Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] Novi Sad, 13 Jan (TANJUG) -- Vojvodina farmers failed to take advantage of the exceptionally favorable weather conditions, not recorded for a long time, to deep-plough almost 1 million hectares of land in preparation for spring sowing. The main reason is the lack of fuel which the farmers expected to receive immediately after the autumn harvest. The province's Secretariat for Agriculture, the Vojvodina Chamber of Economy, and the Vojvodina Cooperative Union note that both the federal and the republic's government have, on several occasions, been asked to secure urgent diesel fuel deliveries but with to avail. [passage omitted]
